HEADWORD: Heterosomati
<hw>Het`e*ro*so"ma*ti</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ other + <?/, <?/, body.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An order of fishes, comprising the flounders, halibut, sole, etc.,
having the body and head asymmetrical, with both eyes on one side.
Called also <altname>Heterosomata</altname>,
<altname>Heterosomi</altname>.</def></p>

